The Hospital-to-Home Transition Program shall provide nonmedical support services to applicants, including but not limited to:
Adult day-care services;
Attendant services;
Home-delivered meal services; and
Transportation services.

The cabinet shall develop a screening tool to determine whether an applicant meets the eligibility criteria under subsection (4) of this section for the Hospital-to-Home Transition Program. The screening tool shall include but not be limited to the following:
Procedures for determining whether an applicant is functionally able to live at home or in a community setting;
Procedures for determining financial eligibility;
Procedures to address patient treatment preferences; and
Procedures to address patient goals of care and family caregiver concerns.
